            <abstract>
                <p>Fourth miracle in <ref type="mss" corresp="ANLcr11"/>, paraphrased according to
                    the descriptions of Strelcyn and Raineri: 
                    A 
                    storm annihilated a band which had organized an
                    attack on the monastery of <placeName ref="LOC3672Gutama">Lagāso</placeName>,
                    where the tomb of the saint is located. The evil-doers
                    wished to force the monks to pay tribute to
                    a warlord of Tǝgrāy. The monks refused due to their poverty. The ruler
                    organised a punitive expedition, but his army was defeated thanks to the intercession
                    of the saint. He alone was able to save
                himself by begging the saint’s pardon.</p>
